<dl id="n40063c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40063c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40063c"> 63(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tritheism / 4th person BVM</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">An exaggerated Trinitarianism or rather Tritheism, a &ldquo;Fourth Person&rdquo; and Saint-worship had virtually dethroned the Deity; whilst Mariolatry had made the faith a <i>religio muliebris</i> &hellip; <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 180</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
